===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
[[File:Square well (Longgang Museum of Hakka Culture).jpg|thumb|井 – an old well in a historic area in [[Shenzhen]]. Notice the square shape.]]
{{liushu|p}} – a square well, with supports on four sides.

Some forms have a stone inside the well, as in [[丼]].

Alternatively, original character of [[刑]], [[形]] and [[型]]<ref>張富海.説“井”[J].出土文献与古文字研究,2021,(00):126-136.
</ref>.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} minimally reconstructs pronunciation *{{IPAfont|tseŋʔ}} for sense "well" and *{{IPAfont|dzeŋʔ}} for "pit" and considers both to be possibly unrelated to each other; furthermore, he relates *{{IPAfont|tseŋʔ}} "well" to {{cog|bo|རྫིང་||pond lake}} and *{{IPAfont|dzeŋʔ}} "pit" to {{cog|bo|སྡིངས་||cavity, depression}}.

